This is no good. I can't tolerate it because I'm too mad.

259
00:17:50,470 --> 00:17:53,020
Auntie, I beg you.

260
00:17:53,020 --> 00:17:55,690
Pretend you didn't see her today and just leave.

261
00:17:55,690 --> 00:18:01,500
No one on set knows that Do Ra and I used to live under the same roof.

262
00:18:02,460 --> 00:18:06,000
Auntie, I'm already having a hard time.

263
00:18:06,000 --> 00:18:09,200
Please don't make it harder. I beg you.

264
00:18:09,200 --> 00:18:11,900
Gosh, I'm going crazy today.

265
00:18:11,900 --> 00:18:14,120
Geez, I'm so pissed!

266
00:18:15,250 --> 00:18:19,990
Auntie! You can't tell Mom about today, okay?

267
00:18:19,990 --> 00:18:21,690
Whatever!

268
00:18:21,690 --> 00:18:23,610
Geez.

269
00:18:23,610 --> 00:18:27,060
Things are hard enough already, but Auntie found out, too.

270
00:18:27,060 --> 00:18:30,070
Geez, why are things getting so messed up?

271
00:18:31,010 --> 00:18:33,740
Don't ever show up in front of me again.

272
00:18:33,740 --> 00:18:36,370
If I catch a glimpse of you,

273
00:18:36,370 --> 00:18:40,380
I swear I'll kill you!

274
00:18:41,380 --> 00:18:43,770
Cut. NG, NG, NG.

275
00:18:43,770 --> 00:18:47,180
Do Ra, you were way too over the top.

276
00:18:47,180 --> 00:18:50,040
And there's no line that says, "I'll kill you."

277
00:18:50,040 --> 00:18:51,310
- There isn't. 
 - Give me the script.

278
00:18:51,310 --> 00:18:54,160
- Let me check the script. 
 - Suppress the emotions a bit.

279
00:18:54,160 --> 00:18:56,840
Let's take a short break and continue.

280
00:18:58,860 --> 00:19:00,550
Geez...

281
00:19:03,400 --> 00:19:06,740
She's letting out her anger directed at me on the scene.

282
00:19:08,020 --> 00:19:11,340
Gosh, she rarely messes up a scene.

283
00:19:11,340 --> 00:19:15,530
She must be furious and feel so betrayed to mess up the scene like that.

284
00:19:15,530 --> 00:19:17,430
Jae Dong, Jae Dong, hold on.

285
00:19:17,430 --> 00:19:19,540
Who are you? Do I know you?

286
00:19:19,540 --> 00:19:21,030
Please let go.

287
00:19:21,030 --> 00:19:22,590
Why are you doing this now?

288
00:19:22,590 --> 00:19:24,750
Jae Dong, please help me.

289
00:19:24,750 --> 00:19:26,820
Please relay a message to Ms. Park.

290
00:19:26,820 --> 00:19:30,310
Tell her I really, really didn't say that because I hated her.

291
00:19:30,310 --> 00:19:35,500
Assistant Director Go Pil Sung, I was behind the sliding door yesterday, too.

292
00:19:37,350 --> 00:19:39,280
You can't do that, Assistant Director.

293
00:19:39,280 --> 00:19:41,800
After hearing what you said about her yesterday,

294
00:19:41,800 --> 00:19:44,730
I felt so hurt that I couldn't sleep all night.

295
00:19:44,730 --> 00:19:49,210
Even I felt that way. Imagine how she must've felt.

296
00:19:49,210 --> 00:19:52,450
I told her not to trust you.

297
00:19:52,450 --> 00:19:56,180
I told her you talk behind her back with Cha Bong Soo,

298
00:19:56,180 --> 00:19:59,400
but she said you'd never do that.

299
00:19:59,400 --> 00:20:02,570
She said you're not like that at all and scolded me instead.

300
00:20:02,570 --> 00:20:06,240
But how could you stab Noona in the back like this?

301
00:20:06,240 --> 00:20:09,060
You shouldn't live like that.

302
00:20:09,060 --> 00:20:11,120
You're a bat.

303
00:20:11,120 --> 00:20:13,880
It might sound like an excuse,

304
00:20:13,880 --> 00:20:16,490
but you understand my position.

305
00:20:16,490 --> 00:20:19,060
I'm at the bottom of the totem pole here.

306
00:20:19,060 --> 00:20:22,470
I have to do whatever the higher-ups say and satisfy everyone.

307
00:20:22,470 --> 00:20:25,440
I can't complain, and I have to follow orders blindly.

308
00:20:25,440 --> 00:20:27,770
That's my job.

309
00:20:27,770 --> 00:20:30,790
You think I did that because I wanted to?

310
00:20:30,790 --> 00:20:35,450
My job is to humor the actors so we could finish the drama successfully.

311
00:20:35,450 --> 00:20:38,340
That's why it happened.

312
00:20:38,340 --> 00:20:41,480
I didn't do that out of animosity.

313
00:20:44,740 --> 00:20:49,920
You know my position as an employee, too.

314
00:20:49,920 --> 00:20:52,270
Of course, that's...

315
00:20:52,270 --> 00:20:55,860
I don't know. I don't know. Don't tell me stuff like that.

316
00:21:05,910 --> 00:21:09,080
 Park Do Ra used to like tteokbokki. 

317
00:21:09,080 --> 00:21:12,260
 Would this spicy tteokbokki ease her anger? 

318
00:21:14,830 --> 00:21:19,600
Ma'am, please add plenty of sauce, too.

319
00:21:19,600 --> 00:21:22,800
I'll have the fishcake to go, too. Please keep it warm so it doesn't get cold.

320
00:21:22,810 --> 00:21:24,310
Okay.

321
00:21:28,150 --> 00:21:30,890
Hyung, what's all this? 
    

322
00:21:30,890 --> 00:21:37,640
Our main investor, Angel Investment's CEO Gong Jin Dan is treating us with hotel-style catering.

323
00:21:39,480 --> 00:21:41,030
Wow...

324
00:21:43,030 --> 00:21:44,720
Did you get something?

325
00:21:46,390 --> 00:21:47,910
Who's that?

326
00:21:58,110 --> 00:22:02,530
What's that? Did President Gong come here himself?

327
00:22:02,530 --> 00:22:04,300
You came, President Gong.

328
00:22:04,300 --> 00:22:05,940
Yes. Thank you for your hard work.

329
00:22:05,940 --> 00:22:08,690
I sent a catering service specifically for you.

330
00:22:08,690 --> 00:22:12,940
I wanted to check if they arrived smoothly and I also wanted to cheer you up.

331
00:22:12,940 --> 00:22:16,030
Everyone was excited about the catering service, anyway.

332
00:22:16,030 --> 00:22:19,060
Thank you so much for being so caring, President Gong.

333
00:22:19,060 --> 00:22:23,090
Thanks to you, the staff and I could cheer up and shoot well today.

334
00:22:23,090 --> 00:22:24,800
Oh, right...

335
00:22:25,640 --> 00:22:27,310
Director—

336
00:22:29,720 --> 00:22:32,024
Leave now. You need to leave quickly.

337
00:22:34,065 --> 00:22:36,565
Do Ra, try the shrimp, too.

338
00:22:37,290 --> 00:22:39,304
- Okay. 
 - It's delicious.

339
00:22:46,004 --> 00:22:47,944
It really is good.

340
00:22:47,944 --> 00:22:50,014
Please enjoy, President.

341
00:22:50,014 --> 00:22:53,154
Wow, is it because it's freshly grilled by chefs?

342
00:22:53,154 --> 00:22:55,564
It's really tender and tasty.

343
00:22:55,564 --> 00:22:57,464
I'm glad you like it, Director.

344
00:22:57,464 --> 00:22:59,554
Help yourself. Fighting.

345
00:22:59,554 --> 00:23:02,194
Yes. Fighting!

346
00:23:11,424 --> 00:23:15,094
Aigoo... Try some.

347
00:23:21,834 --> 00:23:24,204
Thank you, Jae Dong.

348
00:23:26,404 --> 00:23:29,454
I don't need to eat stuff like this.

349
00:23:29,454 --> 00:23:32,104
Please explain things to Ms. Park, okay?

350
00:23:32,104 --> 00:23:36,864
Don't get your hopes up for that. She doesn't forgive people easily once she gets angry.

351
00:23:36,864 --> 00:23:43,604
And go inside somewhere she can't see you. Under the car or something.

352
00:23:43,604 --> 00:23:47,534
She might flip your plate if she sees you, okay?

353
00:24:06,644 --> 00:24:11,784
President Gong, I'm very grateful that you've been so generous,

354
00:24:11,784 --> 00:24:16,254
but I'm embarrassed that I'm always taking it without doing anything for you.

355
00:24:16,254 --> 00:24:18,054
I'm not sure if I can keep taking like this.

356
00:24:18,054 --> 00:24:19,884
What do you mean you didn't do anything?

357
00:24:19,884 --> 00:24:23,564
You're working hard as the female lead of "Straightforward Romance."

358
00:24:23,564 --> 00:24:25,234
And...

359
00:24:27,064 --> 00:24:30,414
I wear this tie all the time.

360
00:24:30,414 --> 00:24:32,074
Pardon?

361
00:24:32,074 --> 00:24:34,734
Tie? What tie?

362
00:24:34,734 --> 00:24:37,014
This tie.

363
00:24:37,034 --> 00:24:38,934
I thought...

364
00:24:38,934 --> 00:24:42,954
you picked this tie for me yourself.

365
00:24:42,954 --> 00:24:44,824
I did?

366
00:24:45,794 --> 00:24:49,114
 Noonim, I received this month's interest. 

367
00:24:49,114 --> 00:24:51,054
 It's so nice we're both keeping our promises. 

368
00:24:51,054 --> 00:24:54,694
You shouldn't have called. I just sent it as I was supposed to.

369
00:24:54,694 --> 00:24:57,804
But I'm grateful you're being so punctual.

370
00:24:57,804 --> 00:25:00,444
Thank you in advance for next month, too.

371
00:25:00,444 --> 00:25:05,154
Don't worry about some silly interest, I said.

372
00:25:05,154 --> 00:25:08,334
 No, no. I'm not worried at all. 

373
00:25:08,334 --> 00:25:11,324
 I'll let you go, then, Noonim. 

374
00:25:15,074 --> 00:25:17,264
I paid the largest interest and...

375
00:25:17,264 --> 00:25:19,544
I paid Ms. Song back, too.

376
00:25:19,544 --> 00:25:24,044
And I sent money to Ms. Ma. Am I done for the month?

377
00:25:24,044 --> 00:25:26,024
Gosh, seriously.

378
00:25:26,024 --> 00:25:29,474
I barely put out the fire with the advance payment for "Straightforward Romance,"

379
00:25:29,474 --> 00:25:32,524
but what will I do next month?

380
00:25:32,524 --> 00:25:35,754
How did I end up in this mess?

381
00:25:42,474 --> 00:25:46,084
 President Gong treated us to a catering service. It was a premium buffet. 

382
00:25:46,084 --> 00:25:51,234
Wow, look how generous President Gong is.

383
00:25:51,234 --> 00:25:55,724
Yes, he's definitely interested in Do Ra.

384
00:25:57,924 --> 00:26:02,084
Yes, President Gong is the ticket to my survival.

385
00:26:02,284 --> 00:26:04,994
If Do Ra and President Gong end up together, having some debt won't be an issue.

386
00:26:04,994 --> 00:26:07,394
If Do Ra and President Gong end up together, having some debt won't be an issue.

387
00:26:11,674 --> 00:26:13,244
Hey, Do Ra.

388
00:26:13,244 --> 00:26:16,034
Yes, I saw the photo of the catering service President Gong paid for.

389
00:26:16,034 --> 00:26:18,884
It looked like he moved a whole hotel restaurant there.

390
00:26:18,884 --> 00:26:22,424
You have to return the favor for this.

391
00:26:22,424 --> 00:26:24,964
Tell him you'd buy him dinner, at least.

392
00:26:24,964 --> 00:26:28,774
Mom, the tie you gifted President Gong...

393
00:26:28,774 --> 00:26:30,974
Did you tell him I picked it, by the way?

394
00:26:30,974 --> 00:26:33,104
Why would you lie about such a thing?

395
00:26:33,104 --> 00:26:34,424
A tie?

396
00:26:34,424 --> 00:26:36,464
Did you say you didn't?

397
00:26:36,464 --> 00:26:38,994
Would I say I picked a tie I've never seen before?

398
00:26:38,994 --> 00:26:42,074
You should've just said you picked it.

399
00:26:42,074 --> 00:26:43,914
Why can't you read the air?

400
00:26:43,914 --> 00:26:46,934
Hey... H-Hello... Hello—

401
00:26:46,934 --> 00:26:49,704
Little brat. How dare she hang up on me?

402
00:26:49,704 --> 00:26:51,104
My gosh.

403
00:26:51,104 --> 00:26:55,684
What if President Gong is disappointed in me?

404
00:27:03,064 --> 00:27:06,914
President Gong, you know the tie I gave you...

405
00:27:06,914 --> 00:27:12,674
I'm so sorry I lied about Do Ra picking it.

406
00:27:12,674 --> 00:27:17,254
Well, did you want to meet to tell me that?

407
00:27:17,254 --> 00:27:20,234
To be honest, I was so smitten with you.

408
00:27:20,234 --> 00:27:23,874
I just wanted things to work out between you and Do Ra.

409
00:27:23,874 --> 00:27:31,024
It did seem like you were slightly interested in her, too, so...

410
00:27:34,194 --> 00:27:38,164
Do you really want me and Do Ra to work out?

411
00:27:38,164 --> 00:27:39,774
Of course, I do.

412
00:27:39,774 --> 00:27:44,254
Although I picked it myself, as far as showing care, I did it with...

413
00:27:44,254 --> 00:27:47,934
a very sincere heart, okay?

414
00:27:47,934 --> 00:27:51,544
President Baek... I mean, Mother,

415
00:27:51,544 --> 00:27:54,944
please help me end up with Ms. Park.

416
00:27:54,944 --> 00:27:58,244
It's true I'm interested in Ms. Park.

417
00:27:58,244 --> 00:27:59,754
My gosh.

418
00:28:00,604 --> 00:28:02,974
Is that true, President Gong?

419
00:28:02,974 --> 00:28:04,484
My gosh.

420
00:28:05,384 --> 00:28:07,964
P-President Gong.

421
00:28:11,054 --> 00:28:15,044
Gosh, seriously. My goodness.

422
00:28:17,514 --> 00:28:20,384
My gosh, look at my glowing skin.

423
00:28:20,384 --> 00:28:23,184
Is it because I've been taking good care of it?

424
00:28:23,184 --> 00:28:25,894
The makeup turned out amazingly today.

425
00:28:27,834 --> 00:28:29,934
Gosh, what's this?

426
00:28:29,934 --> 00:28:31,914
My gosh! My gosh! What's this?

427
00:28:31,914 --> 00:28:33,704
My gosh, what's this? What's this?

428
00:28:33,704 --> 00:28:37,334
My gosh. My gosh, what's this?

429
00:28:37,334 --> 00:28:40,034
Gosh, this is gum.

430
00:28:41,544 --> 00:28:45,174
Ahjumma! Yeoju-daek Ahjumma!

431
00:28:46,984 --> 00:28:48,944
Geez, what's going on?

432
00:28:48,944 --> 00:28:52,764
Yes, w-what's wrong, Senior Madam?

433
00:28:52,764 --> 00:28:55,494
What's wrong? What's going on?

434
00:28:55,494 --> 00:28:59,294
Auntie, look at this. Look.

435
00:28:59,294 --> 00:29:00,994
What's that?

436
00:29:00,994 --> 00:29:02,844
It looks like gum.

437
00:29:02,844 --> 00:29:05,924
Why was there so much gum...

438
00:29:05,924 --> 00:29:08,104
Who did this, anyway?

439
00:29:08,104 --> 00:29:11,034
Who else in this house would do something like this?

440
00:29:11,034 --> 00:29:13,894
Gong Ma Ri! Gong Ma Ri!

441
00:29:13,894 --> 00:29:15,614
Gong Ma Ri.

442
00:29:16,344 --> 00:29:20,554
Did you really put gum on Grandmother's chair?

443
00:29:22,014 --> 00:29:23,604
Yes.

444
00:29:26,624 --> 00:29:28,324
Why?

445
00:29:29,964 --> 00:29:31,784
Why did you do that?

446
00:29:33,064 --> 00:29:36,524
It was because the Second Grandma stressed Mom out.

447
00:29:36,524 --> 00:29:38,864
She kept calling her "Daughter-in-law, Daughter-in-law."

448
00:29:38,864 --> 00:29:41,194
Try to think from her perspective.

449
00:29:41,194 --> 00:29:43,104
How would you feel if your friend called you

450
00:29:43,104 --> 00:29:46,514
"Daughter-in-law" and forced you to call her "Mother"?

451
00:29:46,514 --> 00:29:49,904
I think I'd puke because it's so gross.

452
00:29:49,904 --> 00:29:53,414
My gosh, when did I force her?

453
00:29:53,414 --> 00:29:57,054
But still, Ma Ri, you can't do stuff like this to an adult.

454
00:29:57,054 --> 00:30:01,314
Yes, Ma Ri. You're too old to pull a prank like this.

455
00:30:01,314 --> 00:30:03,204
Gosh, that's enough.

456
00:30:03,204 --> 00:30:06,234
It's because she's sick. What's the point of scolding her?

457
00:30:06,234 --> 00:30:08,834
Grandma, I'm not a fool.

458
00:30:08,834 --> 00:30:11,574
Don't treat me like a fool.

459
00:30:11,574 --> 00:30:13,104
What?

460
00:30:13,104 --> 00:30:16,614
And Second Grandma, don't bully my mom from now on.

461
00:30:16,614 --> 00:30:20,574
I can tolerate other things, but not when someone bullies her.

462
00:30:20,574 --> 00:30:23,774
You'd better not do it again. I'll put glue instead of gum on the chair.

463
00:30:23,774 --> 00:30:27,474
It'd be a super glue. So your butt gets stuck to the chair permanently.

464
00:30:27,474 --> 00:30:29,454
Ma Ri. Ma Ri!

465
00:30:32,774 --> 00:30:35,234
Aigoo, what do we do?

466
00:30:44,024 --> 00:30:47,934
What are you planning to do going forward?

467
00:30:47,934 --> 00:30:53,824
Thinking about the future of the Gong family and the company keeps me up at night.

468
00:30:54,604 --> 00:30:59,704
Auntie, don't worry so much. I have a plan, too.

469
00:30:59,704 --> 00:31:03,574
What's your plan? Yes, tell me. Let's hear it.

470
00:31:03,574 --> 00:31:06,054
We just need a good son-in-law.

471
00:31:06,054 --> 00:31:08,674
We're looking for someone good for Ma Ri

472
00:31:08,674 --> 00:31:11,924
and our family right now.

473
00:31:11,924 --> 00:31:15,634
What? What did you say? Son-in-law?

474
00:31:15,634 --> 00:31:21,684
So, you want to give this company to someone outside of this family that my father,

475
00:31:21,684 --> 00:31:25,224
Oppa, and you have been managing? For three generations?

476
00:31:25,224 --> 00:31:27,654
How does that make sense right now?

477
00:31:27,654 --> 00:31:29,814
What's wrong with that?

478
00:31:29,814 --> 00:31:34,134
We just want Ma Ri to get married and have a child.

479
00:31:34,134 --> 00:31:38,804
Would Ma Ri's child have the last name Gong? Will it?

480
00:31:38,804 --> 00:31:42,484
Ma Ri's child will be my child, too.

481
00:31:42,484 --> 00:31:44,264
What?

482
00:31:45,144 --> 00:31:48,634
Until Ma Ri gets married, has a child,

483
00:31:48,634 --> 00:31:52,764
and the child grows up to inherit the company,

484
00:31:52,764 --> 00:31:56,534
I'll live a long life in good health.

485
00:31:56,534 --> 00:31:59,224
Don't worry so much, Auntie.

486
00:32:00,124 --> 00:32:05,404
I have a meeting. I'll go back to the office and come back.

487
00:32:08,774 --> 00:32:10,724
What?

488
00:32:10,724 --> 00:32:12,484
Son-in-law?

489
00:32:13,204 --> 00:32:16,184
What kind of utter nonsense is that?

490
00:32:21,544 --> 00:32:23,744
- Hyeon Cheol. 
 - Yes, Mom.

491
00:32:23,744 --> 00:32:25,304
What's going on, Hyeon Cheol?

492
00:32:25,304 --> 00:32:26,934
Why did you want to meet outside?

493
00:32:26,934 --> 00:32:29,054
Did something go wrong?

494
00:32:29,634 --> 00:32:32,194
My heart is racing right now.

495
00:32:32,194 --> 00:32:34,064
Nothing went wrong, Mom.

496
00:32:34,064 --> 00:32:35,914
Let me show you something.

497
00:32:35,914 --> 00:32:40,404
Myeong Soo sent me a million won for the dividend. A million won.

498
00:32:40,404 --> 00:32:44,884
- My goodness. You got a million won for the dividend? 
 - Yes.

499
00:32:44,884 --> 00:32:47,614
I think I invested properly this time. I did.

500
00:32:47,614 --> 00:32:52,614
Gosh, Hyeon Cheol. You invested 50 million, but you already got a million?

501
00:32:52,614 --> 00:32:53,934
Yes.

502
00:32:53,934 --> 00:33:00,114
You said the used phone business is a piece of cake in Vietnam.

503
00:33:00,114 --> 00:33:02,194
It must be true, Hyeon Cheol.

504
00:33:02,194 --> 00:33:04,534
I said I was confident this time. I told you.

505
00:33:04,534 --> 00:33:06,674
My goodness.

506
00:33:06,674 --> 00:33:10,164
You would've earned two million if you invested 100 million.

507
00:33:10,164 --> 00:33:12,074
Gosh, what a shame.

508
00:33:12,074 --> 00:33:17,694
I should've gotten 100 million from that woman somehow.

509
00:33:17,694 --> 00:33:22,204
